  %h2(id="201106" style="color: black") June 2011

  .section-grouping
    %h2(id="2011063001")
      30th June 2011: Oz version 0.5.0 now available

    %p
      Oz version 0.5.0 has been released.  Release 0.5.0 is a bugfix and
      feature release for Oz.

    %p
      Highlighted improvements of Oz 0.5.0 are:

    %p
      %ul
        %li
          Replace icicle-nc binary with a shell script to try various methods.
          Besides being more portable, this also allows us to convert Oz to a
          noarch RPM (thanks to Padraig Brady)
        %li
          Support for Ubuntu 6.06
        %li
          Support for md5sum/sha1sum/sha256sum checking of ISOs after download
        %li
          New -x flag for oz-install to write the libvirt XML file to a
          user-specified location (thanks to Steve Dake)
        %li
          Support for OpenSUSE customization
        %li
          Support for F-15 customization (thanks to Steve Dake)
        %li
          Support for running commands at the end of package installation
          (thanks to Steve Dake)

    %p
      More documentation on Oz (including links on how to obtain it) is
      available:

    %p
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
      %a{ :href => "http://www.aeolusproject.org/oz.html",
          :title => "Oz Main Page" } http://www.aeolusproject.org/oz.html

    %p
      For this release, Fedora 14 and RHEL-6.1 packages are available.

  %br

  .section-grouping
    %h2(id="2011062101")
      21st June 2011: Image Factory 0.2.2 now available

    %p
      The Image Factory team is pleased to announce the release of Image
      Factory version 0.2.2.  Version 0.2.2 adds features and bugfixes needed
      to support the next step in the evolution of Aeolus.

    %p
      %ul
        %li
          VMware vSphere support has been added.
        %li
          Support for snapshots of EC2 images on EBS has been added.
        %li
          Importing images from providers has been added to both the command
          line and QMF interfaces.
        %li
          Explicit support for rebuilding images without having to respecify
          the template.
        %li
          Building and pushing images now supports multiple targets or
          providers in a single call rather than requiring one to repeat the
          call multiple times. (added in 0.2.0)
        %li
          Source has been cleaned up and DRYed out.  This is an ongoing,
          iterative process.

    %p
      Download packages from:
      %br
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
      %a{ :href => "http://repos.fedorapeople.org/repos/aeolus/image-factory/",
          :title => "Image Factory repository"} Image Factory repository

    %p
      More documentation will be published at the Image Factory project page of
      the Aeolus site.

    %p
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
      %a{ :href => "http://www.aeolusproject.org/imagefactory.html",
          :title => "Image Factory project page"} Image Factory project page
    %p
      Until then, please refer to the README and documentation
      included with the Image Factory source for more information.

    %p
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
      %a{ :href => "https://github.com/aeolusproject/image_factory/blob/master/README.markdown",
          :title => "Image Factory README"} Image Factory README
      %br
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
      %a{ :href => "https://github.com/aeolusproject/image_factory/tree/master/Documentation",
          :title => "Image Factory documentation"} Image Factory documentation

  %br

  .section-grouping
    %h2(id="2011061501")
      15th June 2011: Image Warehouse 0.96 stable release

    %h3 New features

    %ul
      %li
        %b Added VMware vSphere registration back-end
        %br
        Type is "fs-vmw".
        %br
        %br
      %li
        %b
          The RHEV-M registration back-end can now import a just-uploaded
          template into a master storage domain
        %br
        See new POST parameter "cluster".

    %h3 Bug fixes

    %ul
      %li
        %b
          iwhd will segfault or hang less often during garbage collection
        %br
        [bug introduced in 0.91, partially fixed in 0.94]
        %br
        %br
      %li
        %b
          iwhd init system start script more reliable
        %br
        Prior to this release, the system init script for iwhd would
        mistakenly succeed even if mongod failed to start in time.
        %br
        Now, when mongod fails to start, the iwhd init script also fails.
        %br
        %br
      %li
        %b
          It is now possible to use Windows.Domain\Administrator as a user
          name in a cloud with Windows credentials
        %br
        The backslash was causing an internal error due to improper JSON
        escaping.

    %p Full release announcement with download information:

    %p
