  .section-grouping
    %h2(id="2011060801")
      8th June 2011: Oz version 0.4.0 now available

    %p
      Oz version 0.4.0 has been released.  Release 0.4.0 is a bugfix and
      feature release for Oz.

    %p
      Highlighted improvements of Oz 0.4.0 are:

    %p
      %ul
        %li
          Automatic detection/use of cached JEOS images (the previous method
          required the user of the Oz libraries to detect whether the image
          was cached or not)
        %li
          Fixes to make Debian installs work for both x86_64 and i386
        %li
          Honor user-provided automatic installation files better, by not doing
          modifications
        %li
          Use pyparted to generate partitions on newly created disks (if
          necessary)
        %li
          Add support for Fedora 15
        %li
          Add the ability to supply an initial root/Administrator password to
          the diskimage
        %li
          Abort installs after 5 minutes of disk inactivity
        %li
          Use M2Crypto to generate SSH keys (if necessary)
        %li
          Some pydoc documentation (more of this to come in the future)
        %li
          Support for Ubuntu 11.04
        %li
          Support for RHEL-6.1

    %p
      More documentation on Oz (including links on how to obtain it) is
      available:

    %p
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
      %a{ :href => "http://www.aeolusproject.org/oz.html",
          :title => "Oz Main Page" } http://www.aeolusproject.org/oz.html

    %p
      For this release, Fedora 14 and RHEL-6.1 packages are available.
      Fedora 13 packages are no longer available, as that distribution is
      (or will soon be) out of support.


